data.description: Looking for a property with River access and the ability to keep and use your toys? This is it.    Lovely older home that has been well maintained. Three bedrooms and two bathrooms fit a family or room for guests.  Large rooms and tons of closet space. Indoor laundry room/mudroom and one car garage with storage space.  There are two carports for parking outside of the garage and still protect your vehicles. Covered patio to extend your entertainment options and it includes a large fenced in backyard with a large shed.  And then....the rest of the backyard and side yard are easily accessible to park your camper or boat.  Plenty of space to keep yourself busy or just to enjoy the privacy.  Because the property includes two lots platted together, you also get two deeded access spots on the peninsula to be able to put in your kayak or canoe or paddleboard.  This property has so much to offer and is close to Dunnellon, Crystal River and all the Nature Coast has to offer.  Current VA mortgage is assumable at 3.5% if you are a veteran.
